          "en": "The Q1 2026 all-time first-quarter revenue record and a 21%-above-consensus operating profit beat are clear signals that LG Electronics has crossed a structural earnings inflection point, moving decisively away from the profitability deterioration of 2025. HS and ES divisions are anchoring the earnings base, while the NVIDIA partnership across physical AI, robotics, and data center cooling—alongside surging cooling order wins—is catalyzing a market re-rating of LG Electronics from a traditional appliance and electronics maker to an AI ecosystem participant. Concurrent credit upgrades from S&P (to BBB+, first in approximately 12 years) and Moody's (to Baa1) formally validate the improving cash generation and deleveraging trajectory, marking a meaningful external endorsement of the portfolio transformation. That said, tariff uncertainty, logistics cost inflation, and memory price headwinds remain structural constants that will test the durability of the margin recovery in H2 2026 and beyond. Investors should be aware that a meaningful portion of the current valuation premium reflects forward expectations for robotics and data center cooling contributions that are still years away from material earnings impact; the path of second-half 2026 results and the execution velocity on the new business roadmap will ultimately determine the credibility and sustainability of the re-rating thesis."
